  "text": "Endogenous D2 activity is posttranslationally regulated by its substrate (37, [CITATION_1] , which accelerates its degradation through the ubiquitin-proteasome pathway [CITATION_2] . It was demonstrated that treatment with MG132, a specific proteasome inhibitor, blocked rT 3 -induced down-regulation of D2 activity in rat pituitary tumor (GH 4 C 1 ) cells [CITATION_3] . To study the effects of rT [CITATION_4] and/or MG132 on D2 activity in forskolinstimulated SaOS-2 cells, 10 Ϫ6 m MG132 (Peptide Institute, Inc., Osaka, Japan) was added 10 min before the addition of 10 Ϫ7 m rT 3 . As shown in Fig. 3B , although rT 3 decreased D2 activity, MG132 increased D2 activity 2-fold over that in forskolin-stimulated SaOS-2 cells and blocked rT [CITATION_5] -induced down regulation of D2 activity. These results demonstrated that thyroid hormone inhibited D2 activity in SaOS-2 cells [CITATION_6] . Cells were incubated with forskolin for 6 h, and MG132 was added 10 min before the addition of rT [CITATION_7] . The D2 activity shown represents the mean Ϯ SE of three wells.",
